---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const jsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  name: "Korab Eland",
  url: "https://korabeland.com",
  jobTitle: "CX & AI Strategy",
  email: "korabeland@gmail.com",
  sameAs: [
    "https://www.linkedin.com/in/korabeland",
    "https://github.com/korabeland",
    "https://x.com/korabeland",
  ],
});
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Korab Eland"
  description="CX and AI strategy leader who builds systems that think, based in Melbourne."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="section">
    <article class="article">
      <div class="article-head">
        <h1>About</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>
          I have spent the past twelve years working at the intersection of customer experience, marketing, and operations — most of that at Keypath Education, where I grew from a digital media buyer into the CX Manager for the Australia-Pacific portfolio.
        </p>
        <p>
          The thread through all of it: turning ambiguous problems into clear systems. Whether that was designing a lead scoring model, restructuring cross-functional processes, or figuring out how an AI agent should handle the edge cases that playbooks never cover.
        </p>
        <p>
          Right now I am focused on the operational side of AI — not the research layer, but the messy middle where models meet real business processes and real people. I spend most of my days building with tools like Claude Code, designing evaluation systems, and writing about what actually works when you put AI into production.
        </p>
        <p>
          I care about depth over polish. I would rather show the decisions and tradeoffs behind a project than present a clean outcome with the thinking stripped out. That is what this site is for: a place to share how I work, not just what I have shipped.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of work, I am a runner, a reader, and someone who genuinely enjoys the early phase of a hard problem — the part where you are still framing the question before anyone is asking for a solution.
        </p>
        <p>
          I am based in Melbourne, Australia and currently open to new opportunities in AI operations, product management, and CX strategy — particularly roles where I can bridge the gap between what AI can do and what a team actually needs it to do.
        </p>
        <p>
          If any of this resonates, <a href="mailto:korabeland@gmail.com">send me an email</a>. I am always up for a conversation with someone thinking about similar problems.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
